# Amendment History: github-auto-merge-no-ci-runs

## v1.5.0 (2026-06-03)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus log-analysis remediation session (PRs #901/#903/#904/#906/#908/#910)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed

- Bumped `version` to 1.5.0 (MINOR — new finding, no core rewrite) and refreshed `date`
  to 2026-06-03
- Extended the `description` frontmatter `Use when:` list with trigger (15): `pr-policy`
  fails "Auto-merge is enabled before implementation review GO" on a freshly-armed PR — the
  repo now gates auto-merge behind a `state:implementation-go` label (NOT the old
  propagation race); apply the label with `gh pr edit --add-label` to make the armed state
  compliant
- Added an Overview table row for the 2026-06-03 six-PR label-gated observation
- Added a "When to Use" bullet distinguishing the new `Auto-merge is enabled before
  implementation review GO` error from the old `Auto-merge is not enabled` race, and noting
  that re-running the job alone will NOT fix it
- Added a new subsection "Auto-Merge Gated on an Implementation-Review Label (state machine,
  #899)" explaining the state machine (two valid states: `state:implementation-go` +
  auto-merge ON, or no GO label + auto-merge OFF), the valid label set, and BOTH resolutions
  (apply the label to merge now, or leave auto-merge off / `--disable-auto` to defer)
- Added an **Evolution note** at the top of that subsection cross-referencing and clearly
  distinguishing it from the existing "Required-Check Gate Race" section: the older "just a
  propagation race, re-run it" guidance no longer fully applies on repos that adopted the
  #899 label-gated state machine; on those repos re-running alone will NOT fix it — you must
  align the label with the auto-merge state, told apart by the exact error string
- Added a "Failed Attempts" row: ran `gh pr merge --auto --squash` right after `gh pr
  create` (old habit) → pr-policy Check 2 failed "Auto-merge is enabled before
  implementation review GO" → apply `state:implementation-go` OR leave auto-merge off
- Added a "Verified On" row: ProjectHephaestus 2026-06-03 (6 fix PRs armed before label all
  failed pr-policy Check 2 until `state:implementation-go` applied; label change reran
  pr-policy green; all 6 merged)

### Why

ProjectHephaestus's `pr-policy` CI gate changed in **PR #899** ("Gate implementation PR
auto-merge on review GO", merged 2026-06-03, commit `73b67d3`). This is a NEW behavior that
PARTIALLY CONTRADICTS the skill's existing trigger (11) / "Required-Check Gate Race"
section. Previously a `pr-policy` failure saying auto-merge wasn't enabled was a *propagation
race* — auto-merge IS armed, the gate just read stale metadata, and the fix was to wait or
re-run. After #899, `pr-policy` Check 2 enforces a **state machine** that couples auto-merge
to an implementation-review label: if the PR has the `state:implementation-go` label,
auto-merge MUST be enabled (else FAIL: "PR has state:implementation-go but auto-merge is not
enabled"); if it does NOT have that label, auto-merge MUST be DISABLED (else FAIL:
`::error::Auto-merge is enabled before implementation review GO. Remove it with: gh pr merge
<N> --disable-auto; re-enable only after state:implementation-go is applied.`).

The consequence is that the long-standing habit of running `gh pr merge --auto --squash`
immediately after `gh pr create` now FAILS pr-policy on every PR, leaving it BLOCKED with a
red `pr-policy` check despite all other checks green. The resolution observed to work end to
end was to apply the label — `gh pr edit <PR> --add-label "state:implementation-go"`. #899
made the `pr-policy` workflow rerun on label/auto-merge changes, so the red check turns green
WITHOUT a new commit and the armed auto-merge then fires; alternatively, to defer the merge,
leave auto-merge OFF and add no label (or `--disable-auto` if already armed). Observed across
six ProjectHephaestus PRs (#901, #903, #904, #906, #908, #910) on 2026-06-03: all opened
with auto-merge armed, all failed pr-policy Check 2, all went green and merged after the
`state:implementation-go` label was applied. The valid label set on the repo is
`state:plan-go`, `state:plan-no-go`, `state:needs-plan`, `state:implementation-go`,
`state:implementation-no-go`. Crucially, on a #899-style repo re-running the failed job alone
does NOT fix the failure — the label and the auto-merge state must be aligned.

